The paper discusses the effectiveness of different visualization techniques for geo-temporal multivariate data, which involves both spatial and temporal dimensions. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) for the focus on user tasks and design guidelines, Graphics (cs.GR) for the visual representation aspect, Geographic Information Systems (cs.GEO) for the spatial component, Information Retrieval (cs.IR) for the analysis of patterns and trends, and Databases (cs.DB) for the management and processing of multivariate data.
